data.text:
REPERTORY PHILIPPINES ANNOUNCES CAST OF DISNEY’S CAMP ROCK: THE MUSICAL

Repertory Philippines proudly announces the cast of “ Disney’s Camp Rock The Musical ” which is set to open on November 16, 2012 at Onstage, Greenbelt 1, Makati City.

Disney's CAMP ROCK: The Musical, based on the hit Disney Channel Original Movies Camp Rock and Camp Rock 2: The Final Jam is a fast-moving, engaging love story geared at the tween/teen audience who likes a lot of songs, dances, and a little light romance.

The cast is composed of Morisette Amon who plays the role of Mitchie Torres – a smart, talented, passionate girl who fights for what she believes in.

Markki Stroem shall play the role of Shane Gray, a spoiled pop star Charismatic lead singer of Connect 3, and Mitchie’s boyfriend from last summer.

Nacho Tambunting shall play the role of Nate Gray – Shane’s brother who is a shy boy, drummer of Connect 3.

Jef Flores plays the role of Jason Gray, a comical, easy-going guitarist of Connect 3, Shane and Nate’s brother.

Cheska Ortega plays the role of Tess Tyler, the daughter of rock star T. J. Tyler, the diva of Camp Rock.

Justine Pena shall play the role of Dana Turner – a sweet young girl who is a terrific keyboardist, daughter of Camp Star owner.

Nelsito Gomez plays the role of Luke Williams - A big talent with an ego to match.

Cara Barredo shall play the role of Caitlyn Geller, a quirky and gifted girl, Mitchie’s best friend.

Mica Fajardo plays the role of Ella Pador, a longtime camper who’s very much into fashion.

Bulinggit Delgado plays the role of Margaret "Peggy" Dupree, a loyal Camp Rocker, won last year’s Final Jam.

Kiara Dario shall play the role of Rosie Day, the new girl at Camp Rock.

Justin Valiente plays the role of Barron James, a fabulous hip-hop dancer.

Hans "Triple H" Braga plays the role of Sander Loya, Barron’s best friend and partner in crime.

Karyl Factora shall play the role of Georgina Farlow - a slick, enthusiastic reality TV host.

Eric Mercado shall play the role of Andy Hosten – who is never without his drum sticks.

The ensemble (Camp Rockers/Star Campers) is composed of Jin Dimson, Jazmine Zabala, Alex Reyes, Chaye Magg, Shalee Vicencio, Eddy Thompson, Jim Ferrer, Sam Aquino, Steve Hotchkiss, Kelly Nicolas, Fran Jose, Toinky Lane, Daniel Delgado, Erika Pangan, Aly Wijangco, and Arianna Norton.

A classic story of rivalry and power, Disney's CAMP ROCK: The Musical opens with Mitchie and her friends arriving at Camp Rock, ready to spend another summer jamming out and having the time of their lives. But the new, flashy Camp Star across the lake now threatens Camp Rock’s very existence. To keep the doors open, Mitchie steps up, rallies her fellow Camp Rockers, and gets them into top shape for the ultimate showdown!

With two pop-music summer camps expect a ‘David-vs.-Goliath battle’ that is nothing more serious than a reality show competition between "Camp Rock" (the "good" camp), and "Camp Star" (the “bad camp).

Disney’s Camp Rock: The Musical is from the Book by Robert L. Freedman and Faye Greenberg; Songs by Adam Watts and Andy Dodd and Kara DioGuardi and Mitch Allen and Matthew Gerrard and Robbie Nevil and Dapo Torimiro and Lyrica Anderson and Antonina Armato and Tim James and Thomas Sturges and Toby Gad and Kovasciar Myvette and Aaron Dudley and Steve Rushton and Jamie Houston and Adam Anders and Nikki Hassman and Peer Astrom; and Music Adapted, Arranged, Orchestrated and Produced by David Lawrence.

Disney’s Camp Rock: The Musical is based on a Disney Channel Original Movie written by Dan Berendsen and Karin Gist & Regina Hicks, and on characters created by Karin Gist & Regina Hicks and Julie Brown & Paul Brown.

DISNEY’S CAMP ROCK THE MUSICAL shall run from November 16 – December 16, 2012. All performances are at Onstage, 2/F, Greenbelt 1, Paseo de Roxas cor. Legazpi St., Makati City.

Co-presented by Velvet Channel and the City of Makati, “Disney’s Camp Rock: The Musical ” promises to be an enjoyable treat for the family from the wonderful all-star cast.
